parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The accumulation of condensation and water in the headlight assemblies can cause the bulbs to short out, leading to dim or no light output, which can significantly impair nighttime visibility and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Dim or no light output from the headlights
condensation or water accumulation inside the headlight assemblies
yellow or rust-colored staining on the clear cover
difficulty seeing at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The defective plastic used in the rear light assemblies can cause the tabs to break off, leading to the lights becoming detached from the vehicle body, which can compromise safety and increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rear lights are coming away from the vehicle body
tabs under the top have broken off
lights do not fit the body of the vehicle as designed
lights may change shape and distort under temperature changes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended switching of headlights can cause sudden loss of light output, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Headlights switch to parking lights or turn off unexpectedly
difficulty seeing at night
sudden loss of light output.

the engine fails
the navigation screen sputters and flashes
the controls on the steering wheel stop working
the windows do not close or open automatically
the ABS/traction control/StabiliTrak system malfunctions

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the engine to shut off while driving, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The engine shuts off while driving
the ignition switch is faulty
the key fob or key ring causes the engine to shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door lock system can cause the doors to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to exit the vehicle.

the door lock button does not move to unlock the door
the door must be exited through the passenger side.
